race.comment: Over to the Cup and I AM THE EMPIRE (3) goes on top. He's been racing in excellent form this time in, lugging the 60kg to score in a BM74 at Moonee Valley last time out. This is probably his best sort of trip and it doesn't look an overly strong edition. He'll land in front and take plenty of catching. LINCOLN ROCKS (4) was poor behind I AM THE EMPIRE last time when in the market but had been good prior in a similar race. Looking for improvement. TIKEMYSON (9) was dominant at Geelong two back before a sound effort in the Hamilton Cup last time out. A repeat of that has him in the mix. RICH CHAMPAGNE (6) won the Murtoa Cup when last seen as favourite. This is probably a touch harder but he's going well. COMMANDER HARRY (7) was good in the Coleraine Cup fresh and should only be fitter.
